text:
(1)
East River, showing (right to left) piers 5 to 8, off South Street, from Coenties Slip to Cuylers Alley, as viewed from the New York Telephone Building, 102-108 Broad Street.
August 20, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, at a later date. Also shown (background) is the skyline of Brooklyn. The vantage point is the same as in view No. 1.
August 6, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, at a still later date, as viewed from No. 115 Broad Street.
November 2, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.
title: East River - Piers 5-8 - Manhattan - South Street - Coenties Slip - Guylers Alley.
